  "description": [
    "N L R B WILL SIFT Goodyear Rubber Firm to Get Hearing This Week on Boards Complaint By the Associated Press GADSDEN Ala August 16This industrial city scene of outbreaks of labor violence awaited today an offi cial sifting of charges and counter charges of terrorism made by the United Rubber Workers and Goodyear Tire A Rubber Co Hearing of a formal complaint is sued against the company by the Na ttonal Labor Relations Board was set for Thursday Regional Director Charles N Feidel son said the N L R B complaint was based on information furnished by B T Garner of Gadsden interna tional representative of the Uniled Rubber Workers an affiliate of the Committee for Industrial Organiza tion The complaint charged the com pany with acts of terrorism in an attempt to prevent unionization of its employes The company retorted that the union resorted to coercion in timidation and terrorism in its mem bership campaign The companys answer to the com plaint denied it had discriminated against the union or its members in any manner or form Labor leaders have described Gads den as an armed camp while city officials have insisted the situation was normal and laid"
  ],
